in care\"},{\"title\":\"Supports continuity of care\",\"description\":\"Helps providers understand the story between visits\"}]},\"customer_stories\":[{\"title\":\"\",\"quote\":\"I have been using the  continuous care platform for several months and it has made a big impact in my practice allowing me to monitor my patients more efficiently.\",\"author\":\"Dr. Marie Christina Felix Douyon\",\"role\":\"Pulmonologist, Haiti\"},{\"title\":\"\",\"quote\":\"Allowing doctors to offer telemedicine, remote monitoring health plans, collect payments and the health blog are some of the best features of the Virtual Practice®.\",\"author\":\"Dr. Gerard Saltibus MD\",\"role\":\"General Practitioner, St. Lucia\"}],\"faqs\":[{\"question\":\"What is the Health Journal in the Virtual Practice?\",\"answer\":\"The Health Journal is a secure space inside the patient health record where patients can write free-form notes about their health. Entries can be kept private or shared with their healthcare providers.\"},{\"question\":\"How is the Health Journal different from a regular notes app?\",\"answer\":\"Unlike generic notes apps, the Health Journal is integrated into the patient's health record. When shared, entries are directly available to providers in their clinical view, ensuring secure and relevant communication.\"},{\"question\":\"Can patients control who sees their journal entries?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Each entry can be kept private or shared with healthcare providers connected to the patient's Virtual Practice. Patients have full control over what they choose to share.\"},{\"question\":\"Do providers get notified when patients write new journal entries?\",\"answer\":\"No. Currently, providers only see entries when patients choose to share them. There are no automatic notifications at this stage.\"},{\"question\":\"Can providers respond to patient journal entries?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. When a patient shares a journal entry, providers can add comments directly to that entry. The patient can see these comments, which supports two-way engagement.\"},{\"question\":\"Can the Health Journal be used for symptom tracking?\",\"answer\":\"The Health Journal is best suited for free-form notes. Patients can write about symptoms, progress, or reflections in their own words, but it does not yet include structured symptom tracking or analysis.\"},{\"question\":\"Is the Health Journal part of the patient's official health record?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Entries made in the Health Journal are part of the patient's health record within the Virtual Practice, and shared entries are visible to providers with access to that record.\"},{\"question\":\"Can patients access the Health Journal on both mobile and web?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. The Health Journal is available in the patient portal and mobile app, so patients can add or view entries anytime.\"},{\"question\":\"Do providers benefit from patients using the Health Journal?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Shared entries give providers a more complete picture of a patient's health journey between visits, and provider comments can further guide patient understanding.\"},{\"question\":\"Is the Health Journal integrated with care plans?\",\"answer\":\"Not yet. At present, the Health Journal is a standalone journaling tool within the patient record, but it complements care plans and other engagement features.\"},{\"question\":\"Is the Health Journal secure and private?\",\"answer\":\"Yes. Entries are stored securely within the Virtual Practice platform. Patients control what they share, and sensitive information is protected with the same security standards as the rest of the health record.\"}],\"cta_section\":{\"title\":\"Ready to Capture the Complete Patient Health Story?\",\"subtitle\":\"Transform your clinical insights with patient health journaling that bridges the gap between appointments.\",\"button_text\":\"Start Free Trial\"}},\"device_integrations\":{\"meta\":{\"title\":\"Health Device Integrations | Connected Devices for Conti